The course examines basic concepts related to bankruptcy and their application by the courts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The overall goal of this course is to teach the theory and principles underlying bankruptcy law, and provide students with practical understanding about the conduct of bankruptcy proceedings in court.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students successfully completing this course will be familiar with the theory of bankruptcy law,  will be able to implement the bankruptcy code and its attendant regulatory scheme, and construe them correctly.  The course will also impart the skills and knowledge required for candidates wishing to take the national examination for bankruptcy receivers and trustees.
